post_text:
Dear WMTPS Community,

The shelter in place at WMHS has been lifted. The joint WMHS-WMPD investigation has been completed and the rumor of a weapon in the school has been declared as unfounded. All children are safe and in their classes. I would like to take a moment to thank the WMPD for their effort and professionalism today. Their assistance allowed the issue to be resolved in a timely manner.

Lastly please take a moment to speak to your children about the deleterious effects of social media and the spreading of rumors. As always, if they see or hear something, they should tell a trusted adult such as a parent, teacher, or law enforcement officer.

Best,

Alex Anemone, Ed.D.
Superintendent of Schools
text:
Dear WMTPS Community,

The shelter in place at WMHS has been lifted. The joint WMHS-WMPD investigation has been completed and the rumor of a weapon in the school has been declared as unfounded. All children are safe and in their classes. I would like to take a moment to thank the WMPD for their effort and professionalism today. Their assistance allowed the issue to be resolved in a timely manner.

Lastly please take a moment to speak to your children about the deleterious effects of social media and the spreading of rumors. As always, if they see or hear something, they should tell a trusted adult such as a parent, teacher, or law enforcement officer.

Best,

Alex Anemone, Ed.D.
Superintendent of Schools

West Milford Athletics Hall of Fame Press Release
Now Accepting Nominations!!!

The West Milford Athletics Hall of Fame is excited to announce it is now accepting nominations to the 1st inaugural class of 2018. The Selection Committee will be accepting nominations through November 1, 2017. Nominations can be made by anyone and should include:

-WM athlete
-WM Team
-WM coach
-WM special contributor

To nominate any of the above, please go to www.wmhof.com and click on the nomination form tab. Please email your nomination to joe.trentacosta@wmtps.org or send your completed nomination form to:

West Milford High School
‚ÑÖ Joe Trentacosta - Director of Athletics
67 Highlander Drive
West Milford, NJ 07480

Please visit us on Twitter and Facebook.

West Milford HOF
@westmilfordHOF

https://www.facebook.com/westmilfordhof/

Thank you for being a part of our Highlander PRIDE and tradition!

Sincerely,
Joe Trentacosta

post_text:
At the West Milford Board of Education Meeting on November 17th, the board approved three district goals. One of those goals was described as "Enhancing district climate and culture to foster student achievement and recognition through collaboration with all stakeholders." As a starting point, we believe the surveying of our parents, staff, and students can provide the necessary feedback we need to incorporate the interests and goals of ALL of our community members to build a stronger, student-centered learning environment for all of our schools. Please take a few minutes to complete the school climate survey available at the following web link.

https://docs.google.com/a/wmtps.org/forms/d/1oDSymUEQmVEQkEYlHeeVNDP5UxFLr9k_7b6hlDZLFC4/viewform?c=0&w=1

post_text: We have received an overwhelmingly positive response in regard to our district Acceptable Use Policy. We currently have just over 90% of our student population in agreement. Today's message is meant to inform everyone who has not yet responded that their lack of response will be considered a "yes" in agreement with the Acceptable Use Policy as of Wednesday, October 28th. If you plan on choosing to not accept the terms and conditions of the district Acceptable Use Policy, you must make your selection prior to that deadline. All students who have refused the terms and conditions of our Acceptable Use Policy will no longer be able to access district technology resources including iPads, Chromebooks, and media center or lab computers. If your response remains "No" as of October 28th, the denial of district technology will begin the following day and a letter will be mailed home informing you of this event.

post_text: "Attention students and community members... please listen carefully regarding tomorrow night's football game vs. Lakeland. Know this... there will be a game tomorrow night. However, if threats, poor language through social media or behavior around our towns (the "Rock", etc.) are continued, we will consider CLOSING the event to spectators. West Milford, Wanaque and Ringwood Police Departments are working in conjunction with us, and legal ramifications can occur. Please spread the word to alumni or anyone else who could potentially have a negative impact on this great event for all of us. Students, if you have discipline points, you are reminded that you cannot attend any after school events. All in all, we look forward to an enjoyable contest between two excellent schools. Show Highlander Pride. Be an upstander, lead through positive example. Thank you, and ‚ÄúGo Highlanders!‚Äù

Students, if you have discipline points, you are reminded that you cannot attend any after school events. All in all, we look forward to an enjoyable contest between two excellent schools. Show Highlander Pride. Be an upstander, lead through positive example. Thank you, and ‚ÄúGo Highlanders!‚Äù

The West Milford School District has just been notified that yesterday afternoon on 12/16/14 an older, green Chevy pickup truck approached one of our students who was walking home after getting off his bus.

This was near the intersection of Macopin Rd and Fredrick Drive. The truck approached him, and a male in his late 20s rolled down the window and called to him, "Hey give us your money." When he turned around, the truck also turned around and left. Later that evening he and his parents filed a report similar to this with the WMPD. They have alerted all of the patrol cars to look for this vehicle and have put it out on their daily bulletin.

Please notify the police if you see this or any other suspicious vehicles in the area.

In celebration of this joint endeavor, we would like to open our elementary school doors and welcome parents to join us in the classroom. We are happy to provide West Milford parents with an opportunity to visit your child's classroom in honor of American Education Week on Friday, November 14th, for 30 minutes between the hours of 10:00 AM and 2:00 PM.

Please refer to the school specific information provided about this day (via your child's home school) for further details or call the Main Office of your child's school.

post_text:
Statement by President Inga Koeppe, on behalf of the West Milford Township Board of Education:

We are deeply saddened by the sudden and unexpected loss of our friend and colleague, West Milford Township Board of Education Trustee Valerie McGuinness. Valerie was a lifelong educator, volunteer, and public servant to the students of our district and the entire West Milford community. Our prayers and condolences go out to her husband, Peter, their three beautiful children, and their entire family. As a Board, we will seek to continue Valerie's legacy of dedicated and selfless service to the West Milford educational community. The arrangements are as follows:

Visitation will take place on Wednesday, October 1, 2014, 1-4 and 6-9 p.m. at Richards Funeral Home, 1440 Union Valley Road, West Milford, NJ. The funeral service will take place on Thursday, October 2, 2014, at 11:00 a.m., at the West Milford Presbyterian Church, 1452 Union Valley Road, West Milford, NJ.

text: Please expect a call after 5pm today from our Honeywell Instant Alert System. If you receive the call, no further action is required. If you do not receive a call please contact your child's school tomorrow (Thursday). This is a critical activity that ensures our parents will receive emergency announcements and messages regarding school closings.

Website Update: To make it easier to get to the new Student Portal, we have created a Student Portal button on the quick links menu on the right of the page.

As a reminder, there is no connectivity required between the student portal and the parent portal. The student portal simply reflects the same information that is available on the parent portal.
